issue.title: Conflict with Prometheus version v0.47.0 while using nats lib

labels.name: defect
labels.description: Suspected defect such as a bug or regression

issue.body: ### What version were you using? github.com/nats-io/nats-server/v2 v2.10.1 github.com/nats-io/nats.go v1.30.2 github.com/nats-io/nkeys v0.4.5 github.com/nats-io/nuid v1.0.1 ### What environment was the server running in? Darwin RELEASE_ARM64_T6000 x86_64 ### Is this defect reproducible? Yes Steps to reproduce: - Clone the [opentelemetry-contrib-repo](https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-collector-contrib) - Import the nats lib in the kafka-exporter `factory.go` file - Compile the code with a `otelcol-builder.yaml` file with the changes made, `~/go/bin/builder --config=/Users/tanishabanik/Desktop/projects/project1/project2/project3/otelcol-builder.yaml` ### Given the capability you are leveraging, describe your expectation? Expectation: That the conflict is resolved and helps with successful compilation ### Given the expectation, what is the defect you are observing?

issue.title: Add stream compression option for KV

labels.name: accepted
labels.description: The defect or proposal as been accepted

issue.body:
### What motivated this proposal?

If the KV store is storing similar objects that are repeated compression can save a lot of disk space.
The stream config exposes the compression, but the KV config does not.
Saving disk space and less IO to disk.
Ideally the objects could also be sent over the wire as compressed objects if it is on a per key basis instead of the whole block, but not sure of the implementation. This could be a separate feature request.

### What is the proposed change?

Expose the stream compression option in the KV config.

### Who benefits from this change?

Everyone using KV store

### What alternatives have you evaluated?

_No response_

comment.body:
We've accepted the proposal. We'll also be updaing object sotre with similar behavior: https://github.com/nats-io/nats-architecture-and-design/issues/253

I'll update the go client soon, this should make it into the next release.
